<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: SOROM Battery question.]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=9681&amp;p=105751#p105751"><![CDATA[
Yes, you will need to remove the pin of the RAM chip which does not have backup from VCC line and tie it to the &quot;VCC&quot; pin of the other RAM chip - which is as I called it before &quot;VRAM VCC&quot;, that will be at +5V when the circuit is used, and on the battery's +3V when the circuit is powered off.<br /><br />Also keep in mind that SXROM has 32kb WRAM while SOROM only have 16kb. It could be all right if you develop your game using &quot;only&quot; 16kb though.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=38">Bregalad</a> — Tue Jan 08, 2013 2:17 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
